Identities of some leaders of  'repentant' bandits in Zamfara State given Toyota Hilux vehicles and cash gifts by Governor Bello Muhammad Matawalle have been revealed. SaharaReporters on Wednesday night obtained the names of some of them. The list includes Na Shama, Sani Shaidan, Mohammadu Bello Halilu and Bage Waye. Zamfara State Governor, Bello Matawalle. Other beneficiaries are identified as Kachalla, Ado, Busniya, Dunbulu and Gajere.SaharaReporters had exposed how about 15 brand new Hilux vehicles were given to leaders of different 'repentant' banditry groups by Matawalle.The governor also approved millions of naira to be given to the 'repentant' bandits as compensation."Those bandits have different group, so if they say they repent, the governor will give them a Hilux vehicle; unfortunately they are now using the vehicles to carry out attacks," a military source told SaharaReporters.



